Stephen Poloz has scheduled his first
speech as Bank of Canada Governor on June 19, less than three
weeks after starting the job.  Poloz will also hold a press conference after his remarks
in Oakville, Ontario, according to a  notice  posted today on the
Ottawa-based central bankâ€™s website. No topic for the speech was
listed.  Poloz was named the new governor on May 2 to replace  Mark
Carney , who is leaving to take over the  Bank of England . Poloz,
57, was chief executive officer of Export Development Canada, a
government trade financing agency.  To contact the reporter on this story:
